  {
    "author": "Vittorio Bertola",
    "text": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"677\">@Phillip Hallam-Baker</span>  I think both problems exist - the introduction problem is how do I go from a URI that I get out of band to a window in my client that allows me to send a message to the person at that URI. The authorization/access control problem is how does the user at that URI tell all services and clients whether and how he accepts me sending messages to them. It is conflated because that problem needs to be addressed at the time of first contact between the two users.</p>",
